parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, coolant leaks, and even engine fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: smoke or fumes coming from the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants or other road users.
symptoms: vehicle caught fire while driving or parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant system failures can cause engine overheating, coolant leaks, and engine damage.
Engine component failures can cause engine damage, engine fires, and loss of power.
Exhaust system failures can cause engine damage, exhaust leaks, and engine fires.

Heater core failure can cause hot coolant to leak onto the passenger's floor, creating a risk of burns and injuries. It can also lead to foggy windows, poor visibility, and stalling of the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Hot coolant leaking onto the passenger's floor
and windows fogging up even when the defroster is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heater control valve failure can cause coolant to leak inside the vehicle, creating a risk of electrical shorts and fires. It can also lead to foggy windows, poor visibility, and stalling of the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and windows fogging up even when the defroster is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or refusals in addressing the heater core recall can lead to continued safety risks and financial losses for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to evaluate or repair the vehicle
refusal to reimburse for prior repairs
and difficulties in scheduling appointments for recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or fires. Electrical malfunctions can also cause smoke or fires in the engine compartment, posing a risk to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
smoke or fumes are present in the vehicle
smoke or fire is visible in the engine compartment
the vehicle has a sudden loss of speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause serious injury or death, as well as property damage.
symptoms: Smoke or fire is visible in the engine compartment
the vehicle is engulfed in flames
the vehicle is totaled due to fire damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle will not shift between gears
transmission fails to go into gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch cable failure can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck, or lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Transaxle failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck, or lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: causing shaft to be driven into motor.
